BELLERIAN

SAMUEL BUTLER of Shrewsbury, in his "Ancient and Modern Geography," p.
112, says, "Ocrinum was the Lizard, and B*o*lerium the Land's End."
Ainsworth, Latin Dictionary, 4th edition, has "B*a*lerium --Burien in
Cornwall." It is really in the parish of Sennen.

